    <fr:number>CH1</fr:number>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The differential <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K_\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> is strictly compatible with the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>;
        in other words, the spectral sequence defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex> (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1=E_\infty ]]></fr:tex>) <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.2" />.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:backmatter>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:title text="Context">Context</fr:title>
        <fr:authors />
      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>2630</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:number>8.1.1</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be as in <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-0.3" href="hodge-theory-iii-0.3.xml" number="III.0.3" />.
    Then a <fr:em>Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> consists of

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(ð›¼) &quot;">
        a complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K_A\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+(A)]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^k(K_A)]]></fr:tex> is an <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-module of finite type for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>;
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(ð›½) &quot;">
        a filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K_A\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, i.e. a filtered complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {D}^+F(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>, and an isomorphism <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha \colon  K_\mathbb {C}\simeq  K_A\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {D}^+(\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
            <fr:p>The following axioms have to be satisfied:

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1227</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Axiom</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>CH1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The differential <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K_\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> is strictly compatible with the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>;
        in other words, the spectral sequence defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex> (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1=E_\infty ]]></fr:tex>) <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.3.2.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="1.3.2" />.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1228</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Axiom</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>CH2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k]]></fr:tex>, the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^k(K_\mathbb {C})\simeq \operatorname {H}^k(K_A)\otimes \mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> defines a Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure of weight <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+k]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^k(K_A)]]></fr:tex>, i.e. the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(n+k)]]></fr:tex>-opposite to its complex conjugate (which makes sense, since <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\subset \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>).</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
      <fr:frontmatter>
        <fr:title text="Backlinks">Backlinks</fr:title>
