      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>2631</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-8.1.9.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:taxon>Scholium</fr:taxon>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:number>8.1.9</fr:number>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[K]]></fr:tex> be a mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-complex.</fr:p>
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(i) &quot;">
      On the pages <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_WE_r^{pq}]]></fr:tex> of the spectral sequence of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},W)]]></fr:tex>, the recurrent filtration and the two direct filtrations defined by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> all coincide.
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(ii) &quot;">
      The filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W[n]]]></fr:tex> (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.1.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.1.2.xml" taxon="Definition" number="1.1.2" />) on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}})\simeq \operatorname {H}^n(K_A)\otimes \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> and the filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_\mathbb {C})\simeq \operatorname {H}^n(K_A)\otimes _A\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex> define a mixed Hodge <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>-structure on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(K_A)]]></fr:tex> (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.1" href="hodge-theory-ii-2.3.1.xml" taxon="Definition" number="2.3.1" /> along with <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-0.4" href="hodge-theory-iii-0.4.xml" number="III.0.4" />).
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(iii) &quot;">
      The morphisms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_Wd_1\colon {}_WE_1^{pq}\to {}_WE_1^{p+1,q}]]></fr:tex> are compatible with the Hodge bigrading;
      in particular, they are strictly compatible with the Hodge filtration.
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(iv) &quot;">
      The spectral sequence of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_{A\otimes \mathbb {Q}},W)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2]]></fr:tex> (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_WE_2={}_WE_\infty ]]></fr:tex>).
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(v) &quot;">
      The spectral sequence of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(K_\mathbb {C},F)]]></fr:tex> degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1]]></fr:tex> (i.e. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{}_FE_2={}_FE_\infty ]]></fr:tex>).
    </html:li>


    
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(vi) &quot;">
      The spectral sequence of the complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Gr}_F^p(K_\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>, endowed with the filtration induced by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex>, degenerates at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_2]]></fr:tex>.
    </html:li>

  </html:ol>

  
    
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>690</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">#258</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-258.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:authors /></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The proof of (i), (ii), (iii), (iv) is parallel to that of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.5" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.5.xml" taxon="Theorem" number="3.2.5" />.
      The analogy of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.6" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.6.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="3.2.6" /> and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.7" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.7.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="3.2.7" /> has been taken as an axiom (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch1" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch1.xml" taxon="Axiom" number="CH1" /> and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch2" href="hodge-theory-iii-8.1.1-ch2.xml" taxon="Axiom" number="CH2" />).
      The proofs of <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.8" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.8.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="3.2.8" />, <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.9" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.9.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="3.2.9" />, and <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.10" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.10.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="3.2.10" /> can be carried over as they are, and, as in <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.10" href="hodge-theory-ii-3.2.10.xml" taxon="Lemma" number="3.2.10" />, we thus deduce (i), (ii), (iii), and (iv).
      Claims (v) and (vi) then follow from <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-iii-7.2.8" href="hodge-theory-iii-7.2.8.xml" taxon="Proposition" number="7.2.8" />.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
  
</fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
